# Extra hash-pin patterns for j-rig-binary-eval.
#
# The default audit-harness PATTERNS pin coverage-threshold config under the
# canonical names (.c8rc.json, stryker.conf.json) and dep-cruiser arch configs.
# j-rig declares its coverage FLOOR inside vitest.config.ts instead, so that
# file IS the coverage-policy surface — pinning it makes a silent threshold
# downgrade a HARNESS_TAMPERED event (escape-scan REFUSEs the diff) rather than
# an unnoticed edit. This mirrors how @intentsolutions/core pins its
# coverage-policy surface; the mechanism is the supported per-repo append
# documented in .audit-harness/scripts/harness-hash.sh.
#
# The patterns are bare globs (not globstar-recursive), so a nested
# coverage-policy file must be listed by its explicit path. The scoped
# @j-rig/refiner-core config carries its own dedicated >=80% floor
# (test:coverage:refiner-core lane in ci.yml) and is its own coverage-policy
# surface, so it is pinned explicitly below; a silent downgrade of the
# refiner-core floor is likewise a HARNESS_TAMPERED event.
vitest.config.ts
packages/refiner-core/vitest.config.ts
